joehung302 wrote:
&gt; is it supported?
&gt; 
&gt; Here is the scenerio. Let&#39;s say I checkpoint (thru JMX) every 12
&gt; hours. I have a cron job that checks at every hour to see if heritrix
&gt; is running ok. If not (like OOME) I want to shutdown Heritrix and
&gt; restart it and create a new job based on the last checkpoint all
&gt; through JMX.
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;ve figured out everything except adding a new job based on a
&gt; checkpoint (or recovery). Does 1.6.0 JMX support it?

I haven&#39;t tried it but I don&#39;t see why doing an addJob JMX call against 
the Heritrix MBean wouldn&#39;t work.  Pass an URL that points to a jar made 
from the order and seeds.txt (and any overrides) that are in the 
checkpoint dir you want to recover from (You might be able to just pass 
path to the order file under the checkpoint you want to recover from).
You may have to edit the order.xml so it points at checkpoint directory 
(I think the attribute is &#39;recovery-path&#39;).

If you&#39;re doing &#39;fast checkpointing&#39; (See section 9.4.1 under here 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual.html#checkpoint), you&#39;ll 
have to do some scripting to assemble the bdbje log files before the job 
starts up.  See the manual for whats involved.

Let us know how it goes for you or if you&#39;d like us to add facility to 
jmx recover from a checkpoint (e.g. might make sense to add a recover 
JMX operation).

Good luck,
St.Ack





